<p>I have a model called Alert which has a foreignkey to user (One user can have multiple alerts defined)</p>  <p>Then I have a model called Notice which has a foreignkey to Alert (One alert can have multiple notices)</p>  <p>In some part of my business logic, I need to update a field of All notices that belong to a specific User from which I have the id (I mean, all notices that belong to alerts that belong to this user)</p>  <p>I need to this using the orm like this</p>  <pre><code>Notice.objects.filter(alert__user=1).update(sent=True) </code></pre>  <p>can this be done? without nesting for loops?</p>